"Abstract In this the second article of this series we return to It security perspectives in the Asia-Pacific region; how IT developments are affecting perceptions as to information distribution and security in this dynamic region of business. This time we focus on what has been an interesting IT year for Japan. Not only has 1997 brought the first wave of its very own versions of western Internet service providers — such as Yahoo! and Excite — but coincidentally it has seen a surge in reported virus infections of networks. Japan's IT aloofness may belie a vulnerability, but be sure that the response will be swift. Herein lies a ripe business opportunity for the anti-virus product suppliers — most of whom are western too."
